courses.learning_outcomes:
The purpose of this course is to help students (a) gain a solid understanding of key marketing concepts that are relevant in the context of consumer behavior, and (b) develop good decision-making skills by applying those concepts to real-life scenarios.
This course is relevant to the learning/competency goals of MSc Programme in Marketing:
- Possess a firm grasp of modern marketing theory;
- Be equipped with appropriate analytical and quantitative techniques;
- Be able to adapt marketing strategy to the global environment.

The purpose of this seminar course is to provide students with a basic understanding of marketing practice and issues in China. The course will cover a wide variety of topics relating to China marketing, including:
• the changing environment of the Chinese market;
• marketing competition between international firms and local ones;
• Chinese consumer characteristics and behavior patterns;
• marketing mix management in China;
• Internet marketing in China.
This course will introduce some non-traditional, innovative concepts and approaches for marketing strategies in China. It will help students develop marketing and management skills for doing business in China.

The course is organized around a single customer-centric framework — the customer lifecycle. This general framework emphasizes the design, implementation, and analysis of strategic initiatives in customer analytics, including identifying good prospects and customer acquisition; relationship development through up-selling, cross-selling, personalization, and loyalty programs; customer attrition, retention and win-back. The course also exposes students to analytical “know-hows” — the advantages, limitations, common uses, and best practice — of data-driven tools and quantitative analysis methods, including casual inference, panel data analysis, machine learning, A/B testing and statistical modeling. The principal objectives of the course are:

* To provide a solid foundation in customer-centric marketing;
* To develop fluency and understanding of modern customer metrics and data-driven methods;
* To design and analyze CRM strategies to optimize marketing initiatives and improve firm profitability.

This course will examine the basic conceptual and theoretical framework of brand management, as well as to provide practical approaches to manage brands. Topics covered in this course include the meanings of brand, managing brand equity, brand positioning, brand communication, brand revitalization, brand crisis management, brand protection and global branding.

After completing this course, students are expected:
(1) to understand the essence of a brand;
(2) to be able to assess the strengths and weaknesses of a brand;
(3) to have the ability in formulating a branding strategy; and
(4) to know how to implement a branding strategy

A student who takes this course should be able to:
- Formulate marketing research plan to systematically solve strategic and operational marketing problems;
- Develop the skills to employ critical thinking and data analysis in making optimal marketing decisions;
- Evaluate the advantages and limitations of different data analysis methods for different marketing decisions.

On completion of the course, our students will:

1. understand the current trend and challenges in marketing;
2. learn a systematic approach to solve current marketing problems;
3. demonstrate their problem solving ability through research, presentation and report writing.

Upon completion of this course, students should have:

1. Acquired the core skills and analytical power required to be an effective marketing consultant
2. Acquired knowledge of the latest global environment, industry and technology trends
3. The analytical skills in identify problem and challenges faced by the client company
4. The knowledge in translating a marketing challenge into a feasible project with a plan, a strategy, and deliverables;
5. The skills in applying marketing concepts and methods learned in previous courses;
6. The knowledge of skills in building teamwork spirit with fellow team members, and understand how to work effectively in a project team;
7. Good communication skills through client interaction;
8. Consulting skills in providing solution to solve the problem for the client company and developing recommendations for implementation
9. Strong presentation skills through the final presentation for the client

